":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Llewellyn  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewellyn","meanings":["Welsh: from the personal name <i>Llywelyn</i>, derived from British Celtic <i>Lugubelinos</i>, itself from the divine name <i>Lugus</i> + an uncertain second element often used alone as a name. Through association with <i>llew</i> ‘lion’, it was altered to <i>Llewelyn</i>. This was the name of two princes of north Wales who held the Normans at bay for many years in the 13th century. Etymologically speaking, the form with a fourth <i>-l-</i> is an error, not found as an original Welsh name, but this is now much the most common spelling in the US."]}]},{"name":"Gwynedd","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Taken from a region of medieval North Wales (now resurrected as the name of a composite county in Wales)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gwynedd ap Liewelyn was born in 1011, in North Wales, Wales. He married Edith de Northumberland from 1040 to 1060, in North Wales, Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1011–":"1011–Surnud","1020–Female":"1020–Surnud","1060–Female":"1060–Surnud","1011–Male":"1011–Surnud","1040 to 1060":"1040 kuni 1060","1011":"1011","1020":"1020","1060":"1060","North Wales, Wales":"North Wales, Wales"},"fi":{"1011–":"1011–Kuollut","1020–Female":"1020–Kuollut","1060–Female":"1060–Kuollut","1011–Male":"1011–Kuollut","1040 to 1060":"vuodesta 1040 vuoteen 1060","1011":"1011","1020":"1020","1060":"1060","North Wales, Wales":"North Wales, Wales"},"fr":{"1011–":"1011–Décédé","1020–Female":"1020–Décédée","1060–Female":"1060–Décédée","1011–Male":"1011–Décédé","1040 to 1060":"du 1040 au 1060","1011":"1011","1020":"1020","1060":"1060","North Wales, Wales":"North Wales, Galles","lifeSummary":"Gwynedd ap Liewelyn est né en 1011, à North Wales, Galles. Il a épousé Edith de Northumberland du 1040